# Day 1: C++ Basics (Variables, Input, Output, Conditionals)

## Topics Covered

- Basic program structure
- Output using `cout`
- Variables (`int`, `string`, `bool`, `char`, `double`)
- Input using `cin`
- Reading strings with spaces using `getline()`
- `if`, `else`, `else if` statements
- Comparison operators (`==`, `!=`, `>`, `<`, `>=`, `<=`)
- Logical operators (`&&`, `||`, `!`)
- Modulo operator (`%`)

---

## 1. Basic Program Template

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(NULL);
    
    // your code goes here
    
